trans-unit.source: Finding a location for your photo printer
trans-unit.target: Finding a location for your photo printer

trans-unit.source: Place the photo printer on a flat, clean and dust-free surface, <cf bold="on">in a dry location</cf>, and <cf italic="on">out of direct sunlight</cf>.
trans-unit.target: Place the photo printer on a flat, clean and dust-free surface, <cf bold="on">in a dry location</cf>, and <cf italic="on">out of direct sunlight</cf>.

trans-unit.source: Allow at least 12 cm clearance from the back of the photo printer for the paper to travel.
trans-unit.target: Allow at least 12 cm clearance from the back of the photo printer for the paper to travel.

trans-unit.source: When
trans-unit.target: When

trans-unit.source: connecting power or USB cables, keep the cables clear of the paper path to the front and rear of the photo printer.
trans-unit.target: connecting <cf highlight=yellow>power </cf>or USB cables, <cf underlinestyle="single">keep the</cf> cables clear of the paper path to the front and rear of the photo printer.

trans-unit.source: For proper ventilation<footnotereference style="Footnote Reference" autonumber="1"/>, make sure the top and back of the photo printer are not blocked.
trans-unit.target: For proper ventilation<footnotereference style="Footnote Reference" autonumber="1"/>, make sure the top and back of the photo printer are not blocked.

trans-unit.source: Allow enough
trans-unit.target: Allow enough space on all sides of the photo printer to let you connect and disconnect cables, change the color cartridge, and add paper.

trans-unit.source: Connecting and turning on the power
trans-unit.target: Connecting and turning on the power

trans-unit.source: Note:
trans-unit.target: Note:

trans-unit.source: Use only the AC power adapter included with your photo printer.
trans-unit.target: Use only the AC power adapter included with your photo printer.

trans-unit.source: Other adapters can damage your camera, photo printer, or computer.
trans-unit.target: Other adapters can damage your camera, photo printer, or computer.

trans-unit.source: To connect and turn on the power, follow these steps:
trans-unit.target: To connect and turn on the power, follow these steps:

trans-unit.source: Step
trans-unit.target: Step

trans-unit.source: Notes
trans-unit.target: Notes

trans-unit.source: Connect the AC power cord to the AC power adapter, then to the back of the photo printer.
trans-unit.target: Connect the AC power cord to the AC power adapter, then to the back of the photo printer.

trans-unit.source: The AC power cable included with your photo printer may not require assembly, and may be different from the one shown.
trans-unit.target: The AC power cable included with your photo printer may not require assembly, and may be different from the one shown.

trans-unit.source: Plug the AC power cable into a power outlet.
trans-unit.target: Plug the AC power cable into a power outlet.

trans-unit.source: Press the On / Off button to turn the power on.
trans-unit.target: Press the On / Off button to turn the power on.

trans-unit.source: The photo printer initializes and the On/Off button glows steady green.
trans-unit.target: The photo printer initializes and the On/Off button glows steady green.
